Ahh Chet, see what happens when you get international fame and accolades from CNN, you get to smart for words.  Keep it quiet about my using my &quot;spoon&quot; will ya?<br><br>
Joe, before you get to sensitive about &quot;teachers&quot;, that was not the point of my attack on the good nurse. In fact I also have a teaching credential, college level too. You will need to go way back in the archives to understand why many of us got quite pissed off at Nurse Ratchet, or live with a very brief recap (cause that's all he is worse).<br><br>
The Nurse admitted that he was a high school teacher in a &quot;bad neighborhood&quot; and felt that was the moral equal of being in the jungle (like a vet), and also stated that he had &quot;protested with my vote&quot;. I.E. he was nothing during the Vietnam issue, not a soldier, not a protestor, not even a sunday marcher or once a year protest rally boy. He was just the silent majority that helped the war continue and kill and maim more and more, while he sat on his rosie high lotto number and did NOTHING.  That is the point. He didn't have a side then, and now, he comes across as wanting to be the expert.  The Nurse got nailed alot, not just by me, and fled.  Now, after a few months, and probably because the site has gotten significant publicity, he returns wanting once again, a piece of the action he ran from. <br><br>
So Joe, relax, sure he has freedom of speech, but in his case, it is freedom to shot off his own foot, step on his onw d---(private part), or continue to expose his &quot;bravado&quot; while the rest of us laugh and resent him. Laugh because he is a clown. Resent because he can't seem to learn anything from others, and that makes me feel real bad for his students.  Oh, by the way, in the archives you will find that someone even asked him to present the dialogues to his students, and let them write in.  Clearly he never did, and no one, no one, oh the silence was deafing, came to his defense.<br><br>
Finally, I realize that in only 7 months this site has developed history, that some posts have long strings attached, and of course, you would not know that. No attack was ever intended on teachers, or &quot;teacher-boy&quot; or anyone other than the person who uses a pseudonom, Nurse Ratchet, which is dispicable in itself. Remember the character of the Nurse in the Movie: One Flew Over the CoCoo'(sp?) nest? The Nurse that ended up doing electroshock to the real hero, Mc Murfy (Jack Nicholson)?  That dictatorlike, castrating, mean spirited Nurse Ratchet is who our buddy uses as his nickname. I mean what does that tell you about the cynical SOB behind the mask?  I, for one, always sign my name and my address. It just is how I do things. Others don't, but the others don't pick a slightly &quot;controversial&quot; label to hide behind.  Anyone who has ever been inpatient would, I assume,<br>
be likewise insulted by it.  I'm in the mental-business, I sure am.  More than enough said.
